<div id="Idea_4443"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4443-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4443">Mandatory voting for all members of Congress&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/11776-4049">Martin Snider</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">14 minutes ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Change the congressional rules or the constitution if necessary to require every member of congress to vote yea, nay, or abstain on every vote in the House or Senate.  Eliminate requirement of physical attendance.  Vote must be confirmed by legislator's office, if not in attendance.  Allow for changing one's vote after the final result only in the event of technical malfunctions or vote tampering (which should be a major felony).</div>
