<div id="Idea_4426"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4426-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4426">Obama's citizenship&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/11660-4049">nuss</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 hour ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The vast majority of Americans (greater than 99.99999...%) have no idea whether Obama is a natural born citizen of the United States.  Americans have the right to know.  It's not just about the Hawaiian birth certificate, which has not been made public, there is also the problem that his father was a British (Kenyan) citizen when Obama was born, and his mother was not old enough to confer American citizenship on their son. Therefore, even if Obama was born in Hawaii, he was a British Citizen at birth.  To complicate matters, Obama attended school in Indonesia under the name of Barry Soetoro in schools that listed him as a citizen of Indonesia.  Therefore, there are at least three ways that Obama may not be a citizen of the United States, or at least a natural born citizen.</div>
