<a href="/akira/dtd/4385-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4385">Power of knowledge.&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/11268-4049">Heidi </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">2 hours ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Every U.S. citizen should know some of the basic laws.  Sometimes a person might not even be aware that they could be breaking a law.  Even the police  do not fully know their own states laws.  Maybe a class in school should be mandatory, or print free pamplets informing people of their rights and the local laws.  The town could post them in the library, post office, interent, etc.  <br/><br/>Who taught me the laws that I know, my parents?  How does a child comply to the law when their own parents do not follow the laws?  What will a person know what to do if they weren't taught rigth from wrong.  Give people the power to know their laws and how to follow them.</div>
