<a href="/akira/dtd/4112-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4112">Require Mental Evaluations for everyone running for president to determine if they have a serious personality disorder&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/7012-4049">lpr300</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">after the events of the past eight years, i realized it was foolish for us to fail to screen people asking to represent america to the world and to significantly change our country and the world by doing so.  It appears, given the behaviors of Nixon, Bush, and Cheney to name a few, that we allow people to run for this office who may be narcissists, sociopaths, pathological liars, or psychopaths.<br/><br/>i recommend a team of three well respected psychaitrists evaluate candidates.  one to be chosen by the candidate, one by a citizen committee, and one by the FBI.<br/><br/>these three should work independently and provide the results of their tests in an open format, simultaneously to the public.<br/><br/>people with these emotional / mental illnesses are often charismatic and will do anything to achieve their goals.  we need to know if our leaders are mentally and emotionally healthy.</div>
