<div id="Idea_4109"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4109-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4109">Stop the privatization of the education system&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9740-4049">cbishopp</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Parents and children suffer from the rising cost of education and the loss of quality within the public system.<br/>No Child Left Behind was a key step in ruining the public education system by equating performance test scores with the budget a school would be allotted for the following year by the Federal Government. As a result key programs were cut, falsification of records and test scores by teachers increased, and children were taught the test and the strict curriculum ascribed therein.<br/>More and more the education of our children is equated with and driven by economic factors. This system is failing to establish a well rounded constructive classical education for our children and with teacher's salaries actually falling and the cost of living increasing we are losing quality teachers and the ability to assist student's individually in classrooms of increasing size further plagues our schools.<br/>As a result many people have turned to a private education as the best way to deal with this problem. I believe this further alienates communities and raises the cost of education unnecessarily to a staggering fee.<br/>In California, parents of preschool students pay up to $20,000 a year for educational services. This begins at such a young age because each school or institution has a tailored education and recommendations for the next school. So a good preschool leads to a good grammar school to a good junior high to a good high school. Now parents are paying what used to be the amount spent on a college education for high school and fewer families each year can assume such costs.<br/>Why are we giving money to banks when they loan it back to us at interest when we can create a government bank that can loan money out to schools at a deferred interest. Interest that, when paid, would further assist in building the very school system to which the money is loaned. Why can't we invest in community education? </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_4109" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_4109', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=4109')">Comments (4)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_4109"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_4109"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_4099">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_4099">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_4099', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=4099&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 1 day ago</div><div>Votes For : 41</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_4099'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_4099" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 1 day ago</div><div>Votes For : 41</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_4099'))">35</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_4099', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=4099&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
