<div id="Idea_4086"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4086-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4086">Investigate and prosecute war crimes&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/8602-4049">bobschacht</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Abundant evidence exist that the Bush Administration committed war crimes. The Spanish Court is investigating these alleged crimes-- but from our compromised Department of Justice, only crickets. We voted for change we can believe in, but what we have seen from AG Holder's DOJ seems mostly to be locked into President Bush's positions. <br/><br/>It is also a war crime to fail to investigate and prosecute war crimes. Unless AG Holder acts soon, he risks becoming a war criminal himself. <br/><br/>The time to restore our national values is now. We must decisively reject war crimes, and hold responsible those who have committed them, with appropriate prosecution. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_4086" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_4086', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=4086')">Comments (5)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_4086"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=war crimes">war crimes</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=justice">justice</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=american values">american values</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_4086"></div>
